| Step | What happens | Why it matters |
|------|--------------|----------------|
| **setupTestServer** | Spins up a fresh in‑memory SQLite DB, runs migrations, creates all repositories, use‑cases and HTTP handlers, and returns an `httptest.Server`. | Guarantees isolation – no state leaks between tests (see *test_infrastructure*). |
| **createCategory** | Calls `POST /categories` (handler `CategoryHandler.Create`). The test asserts `201 Created` and extracts the generated `id`. | Validates the *Category* use‑case (`CategoryUseCase.Create`) and repository (`CategoryRepository.Create`). |
| **createProduct** | Calls `POST /products` with the previously‑created `category_id`. Asserts `201 Created` and extracts the product `id`. | Checks that the *Product* use‑case validates the product and that the category existence check works (`ProductUseCase.Create`). |
| **createOrder** | Calls `POST /orders` with `customer_id` and an `items` array that references the product. Asserts `201 Created` and extracts the order `id`. | Triggers `OrderUseCase.Create`, which validates the order, looks up product price, fills `OrderItem.Price`, and runs `CalculateTotal()`. |
| **GET order** | Retrieves the order (`GET /orders/{id}`) and verifies `Total` and initial `Status = new`. | Confirms that the total was correctly calculated (`Order.CalculateTotal`) and that the order starts in the `new` state. |
| **process** | Calls `PUT /orders/{id}/process`. Asserts `200 OK`. | Executes `OrderUseCase.Process`, which checks `CanCancel/CanComplete` logic and updates status to `processing`. |
| **complete** | Calls `PUT /orders/{id}/complete`. Asserts `200 OK`. | Executes `OrderUseCase.Complete`, which only succeeds when the order is in `processing`. |
| **final GET** | Retrieves the order again and checks `Status = completed`. | Verifies the full state‑machine transition (`new → processing → completed`). |

