	getAfterComplete := doRequest(t, http.MethodGet,
		srv.URL+"/orders/"+fmt.Sprint(order.ID), nil)
	require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, getAfterComplete.Code)

	var afterComplete struct {
		Status string `json:"status"`
	}
	decodeBody(t, getAfterComplete.Body, &afterComplete)
	require.Equal(t, "completed", afterComplete.Status)
}
```

### What the test does

| Step | Action | API endpoint | Expected result |
|------|--------|--------------|-----------------|
| 1️⃣ | Build a fresh server | `setupTestServer(t)` | Isolated in‑memory SQLite, all handlers wired |
| 2️⃣ | Create a category | `POST /categories` | `201 Created`, JSON with `id` |
| 3️⃣ | Create a product (belongs to the category) | `POST /products` | `201 Created`, JSON with `id` |
| 4️⃣ | Create an order (uses the product) | `POST /orders` | `201 Created`, status = `"new"` and correct total (`price * qty`) |
| 5️⃣ | Process the order | `PUT /orders/{id}/process` | `200 OK` → status becomes `"processing"` |
| 6️⃣ | Complete the order | `PUT /orders/{id}/complete` | `200 OK` → final status `"completed"` |

